Uses of Interface
com.picocontainer.Parameter

  • Packages that use Parameter 
    Package Description
    com.picocontainer
    This package contains the core API for PicoContainer, a compact container for working with the dependency injection pattern.
    com.picocontainer.classname  
    com.picocontainer.containers
    Containers are the main user entry point for PicoContainer.
    com.picocontainer.injectors
    InjectionFactories make Injectors which implement specific types of dependency injection.
    com.picocontainer.parameters
    In the PicoContainer API, Parameters are used for specifying which constructor argument (or setter argument) goes where.
    com.picocontainer.security  
    com.picocontainer.visitors
    This package contains various implementations of visitors.

      Classes in com.picocontainer.parameters that implement Parameter 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  AbstractParameter 
      class  AnnotationCollectionComponentParameter
      Will match all objects as parameters that have the given class-based annotation marker.
      class  BasicComponentParameter
      A BasicComponentParameter should be used to pass in a particular component as argument to a different component's constructor.
      class  CollectionComponentParameter
      A CollectionComponentParameter should be used to support inject an Array, a Collectionor Mapof components automatically.
      class  ComponentParameter
      A ComponentParameter should be used to pass in a particular component as argument to a different component's constructor.
      class  ConstantParameter
      A ConstantParameter should be used to pass in "constant" arguments to constructors.
      class  DefaultConstructorParameter
      Part of the replacement construct for Parameter.ZERO
      class  JSR330ComponentParameter
      Extension to ComponentParameter that attempts to sort out "ambiguous components" in a way compatible with JSR330.
      class  NullParameter
      Once in a great while, you actually want to pass in 'null' as an argument.
